CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 21, 1956, pg. A12, reads: "Making 'Dough' - Mr. Taddings and his boys display the tasty pastries they prepared in their bake shop, which is one of the most modern and well-equipped bakeries in the city.  The class is made up of transfers from South High School and Korean War veterans. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Boys, young men, and men, possibly including Mr. Taddings, posed behind large table of baked goods in bakery classroom at South Vocational High School
